"{\n    \"Title\": \"Notes to the Consolidated Financial StatementsFor the year ended March 31, 2020\",\n    \"row 1\": \"2. Significant accounting policies (Continued from previous page)\",\n    \"row 2\": \"Revenue recognition\",\n    \"row 3\": \"Other revenue\",\n    \"row 4\": \"Other revenue, such as rental income, is recognized when service is provided and collectability is reasonably assured.\",\n    \"row 5\": \"Government Transfers\",\n    \"row 6\": \"The First Nation recognizes a government transfer as revenue when the transfer is authorized and all eligibility criteria, if\",\n    \"row 7\": \"any, have been met. A government transfer with stipulations giving rise to an obligation that meets the definition of a liability\",\n    \"row 8\": \"is recognized as a liability. In such circumstances, the First Nation recognizes revenue as the liability is settled. Transfers of\",\n    \"row 9\": \"non-depreciable assets are recognized in revenue when received or receivable.\",\n    \"row 10\": \"Deferred revenue\",\n    \"row 11\": \"Deferred revenue consists of unspent contributions for programs which are not complete at year end. The unspent revenue\",\n    \"row 12\": \"is carried forward to be matched against expenses to be incurred in the subsequent year.\",\n    \"row 13\": \"Use of estimates\",\n    \"row 14\": \"The preparation of consolidated financial statements in accordance with Canadian public sector accounting standards\",\n    \"row 15\": \"requires management to make estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities and\",\n    \"row 16\": \"disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities at the date of the consolidated financial statements, and the reported amounts\",\n    \"row 17\": \"of revenue and expenses during the reporting period.\",\n    \"row 18\": \"Accounts receivable is stated after evaluation as to their collectability and an appropriate allowance for doubtful accounts is\",\n    \"row 19\": \"provided where considered necessary. Amortization is based on the estimated useful lives of tangible capital assets.\",\n    \"row 20\": \"Accounts payable and accruals are based on historical charges for unbilled goods and services at year-end.\",\n    \"row 21\": \"These estimates and assumptions are reviewed periodically and, as adjustments become necessary they are reported in\",\n    \"row 22\": \"earnings in the periods in which they become known.\",\n    \"row 23\": \"Segments\",\n    \"row 24\": \"The First Nation conducts its business through ten reportable segments: Administration, Capital, Economic Development,\",\n    \"row 25\": \"Education, Governance, Health, Housing CMHC, Ontario First Nations Limited Partnership, Operations and Maintenance,\",\n    \"row 26\": \"and Social Services. These operating segments are established by senior management to facilitate the achievement of the\",\n    \"row 27\": \"First Nation's long-term objectives to aid in resource allocation decisions, and to assess operational performance.\",\n    \"row 28\": \"For each reported segment, revenue and expenses represent both amounts that are directly attributable to the segment and\",\n    \"row 29\": \"amounts that are allocated on a reasonable basis. Therefore, certain allocation methodologies are employed in the\",\n    \"row 30\": \"preparation of segmented financial information.\",\n    \"row 31\": \"The accounting policies used in these segments are consistent with those followed in the preparation of the consolidated\",\n    \"row 32\": \"financial statements as disclosed in the significant accounting policies.\",\n    \"row 33\": \"3. Cash resources\",\n    \"row 34\": \"2020 2019\",\n    \"row 35\": \"Royal Bank - GIC (interest at 1.80%, matures April 15, 2020) 8,500,000 -\",\n    \"row 36\": \"Royal Bank - General Account 392,010 428,624\",\n    \"row 37\": \"Bank of Nova Scotia - Social Services Account 133,434 101,629\",\n    \"row 38\": \"Royal Bank - Water Treatment 73,427 -\",\n    \"row 39\": \"Guaranteed Investment Certificate 8,248 8,249\",\n    \"row 40\": \"9,107,119 538,502\"\n}"